Java Developer

Our Client in Cary, NC is looking for a developer to be on a small project teams (Product Strategy Team or PST) that develop procurement applications.  PSTs use agile software development principles to build great products that serve the needs of our customer base– gathering and reviewing user requirements, database and application design, coding, testing, maintenance, internal and external customer training and product rollout.

 

The developers on the team contribute primarily through programming expertise, but are expected to be an integral part of all team activities.  Additionally, developers are expected to work with other Product Strategy Teams (who work on the same product) to ensure continuity of architecture and design.

 

You will start building production ready software right away!

Principal Responsibilities:
  • You are going to be an important participant in user story creation and sprint planning activities.
  • You will design, code, test and debug software during our agile, sprint based releases – using documented user stories and close team communication as a guide.
  • Good software stewardship (things like solid OO design and responsible refactoring) is important to us.
  • You will be a critical participant in defining and implementing technical direction for your team’s projects.
  • We want you to lead the team toward designing intuitive, user-friendly interfaces.
  • Based on your experience, we want you to suggest areas for improvement in internal processes along with possible solutions.
  • You will have a chance to contribute to our library of development components and frameworks.
  • We hope that you will enjoy participating in Usability Studies with our customers.  (We do.)
  • Sometimes, we’ll need you to troubleshoot and maintain production code (but you are going to really appreciate the Production Support Development team for handling the day to day fires that pop up).
Position Requirements:
  • Excitement for learning and for building software as part of a small, focused team
  • Excellent communication, organization and interpersonal skills
  • A good sense of humor (we try not to take ourselves too seriously)
  • Working knowledge and experience using Java, JavaScript, Servlets, JSP, HTML and CSS
  • Good working knowledge of relational databases, database design and SQL is critical
  • Additionally, knowledge of XML, JSON and other web programming technologies are great
  • Experience building web-based applications is important (even if it’s not with our technologies)
  • We are looking for 2+ years experience developing software
  • A Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field is helpful

The Government Solutions Product Development team is a mature software development shop that builds, creates, and supports multiple products for our clients in solving their Human Capital Management needs. Our product managers and development team leads work jointly to plan, staff and enforce quality on development projects.

 

We currently are seeking a Software Engineer that will report to the Manager of Development.

 

PURPOSE OF JOB:

  • Through best of breed customer service work within a matrixed organization on a dedicated team as we build the next generation of scalable Human Capital Management software. You’ll work with Oracle 11g, Tomcat, Java 1.6, JSP’s, and Web 2.0 technologies in a true software development environment.


RESPONSIBILITIES

  • Create, update and maintain Java objects, JSP’s, taglibs and core business logic.

  • Enforce best of breed database, persistence and Java code
  • Build and test for Oracle 11g

  

REQUIRED SKILLS:

  • Bachelor’s degree in computer science.
  • At least five years of experience must be with a top tier web software firm.
  • Experience with Java persistence layers
  • Experience with Object Oriented Principles and Design Patterns
  • Experience with Oracle Stored Procedures
  • Ability to work in a team-oriented environment.
  • Superior problem solving skills.
  • Analytical skills – Ability to assess a situation quickly from a non-biased point of view, and determine the most beneficial resolution for all parties involved.
  • Organization skills – Ability to track unresolved issues and bring them to resolution is essential.  The ideal candidate will take the initiative to follow up and, if necessary, escalate issues in order to bring them to a conclusion.
  • US Citizenship or Green Card

 

PREFERRED SKILLS:

  • Java certified.
  • Preference for experience with high availability architectures.
  • Preference for experience with secure government information systems,  and/or ERP systems.
  • Experience in ASP/hosted environments.

A Fortune 500 company, PNC is one of the largest and most respected banks in the country. But that doesn't mean we speak in banking lingo or hide behind spreadsheets. In fact, it's our down-to-earth approach with customers that's put us on the map.

We see how work/life balance, green initiatives, a family-friendly outlook, and social responsibility make for happier employees. And happy employees make for very happy customers.

As a Java Developer and a member of PNC's Information Technology group, you will be part of a diversified financial services firm that reflects the needs, values and goals of our customers, employees, communities and shareholders. You will be instrumental in helping to maintain PNC's reputation for technology excellence in both business applications and new innovations. Your area is responsible for performing application software development for system enhancements, potentially across a variety of technology platforms. As an integral part of this dynamic and progressive team, you will develop basic application software for system enhancements, possibly across a variety of technology platforms. You will also assess and determine design considerations, which include application programs that contain the business logic, and possibly modify databases, client reports, internal reports and online presentations.

This position combines autonomy with leadership support while you develop plans for system testing that ensure a quality product is presented to PNC Lines of Business (LOB) for acceptance. Through integrity, teamwork and customer focus, you will help reinforce our product-specific goals and concepts to drive value to each LOB. Because PNC not only acquires great talent but also develops them organically, you will work under the guidance of senior engineers and your manager to augment your skills on such projects as system enhancements and operational and technical support for routine and non-complex system functions for our LOB service partners.  This position will be based in Pittsburgh, PA. 

Responsibilities include but may not be limited to the following:

* Previous experience as a application programmer on successful, enterprise level information technology projects

* Experienced in working in a team environment developing software, testing and deploying public facing websites

* Ability to follow detailed project plans and activity assignments respecting (scope, schedules, processes and work breakdown structures)

* Experience in developing system and user documentation

* Experience in delivering the project tasks on the agreed upon schedule, to the correct technical specification

* Experience with software development tools specifically JAVA, Oracle, and Web Sphere in a Unix environment

* Experience working with Spring, Hibernate, Struts2, Oracle, SQL, XML, Tag Libraries, & JSPs is a plus

* Experience in integration of multiple systems or applications

* Follow test plans for unit and system tests.

* Create documentation based on corporate documentation guidelines

* Experience with UI/Graphical Interface tools and/or UI development a STRONG plus

 

Required Skills:

* Bachelor's degree or equivalent in an IT-related field

* 2-4 years related experience.

* Possess a strong understanding of IT concepts including database concepts structures, software/application development techniques and testing techniques.

* Develops a strong understanding of core technologies contained within the LOB application supported.

* Strong verbal and written communications skills

 

PNC is committed to offering you a comprehensive and competitive benefits package. We design our full-time and part-time benefits programs based on PNC's benefits philosophy to provide quality levels of coverage at affordable costs over the long term for both employees and PNC. We strive to balance the cost of providing competitive benefits with the need to cover employees with a wide range of protection during and after employment.

\r

  

\r

Programming Specialist:

\r

Under general supervision, the incumbent determines technical user requirements and plays a key role in the development and installation of computer applications to fulfill these requirements.  Participates in project planning, analysis, design, coding, code review, unit/system testing, test scripting, and installation of software applications.

\r

  

\r

•             Produce effective, highly reusable and maintainable software application design by using best practices, design patterns, and OOAD methodology.

\r

•             Resolve critical problems under pressure and under significant time constraints.

\r

•             Meet with customers to analyze, gather, and document user requirements paying special attention to interfaces with other systems.

\r

•             Determine project scope and risk factors.

\r

•             Prioritize multiple projects simultaneously.

\r

•             Communicate with all project stakeholders on a regular basis.

\r

•             Participate in code reviews, shared modules, reusable components and various enterprise architectural decisions.

\r

•             Perform unit and system testing and create/maintain test scripts.

\r

•             Prepare user documents and train new users on software applications.

\r

•             Provide on call support as needed.

\r

  

\r

\r

\r

  

\r

\r

•             Determine source data (input), processing requirements (output), output formats, timing and cost estimates.

\r

•             Verify that system meets performance criteria.

\r

•             Design, implement, and document procedures.

\r

•             Design/modify, code, debug, test, and document moderately complex application systems.

\r

•             Install and test moderately complex software packages.

\r

•             Training users in new applications.

\r

•             Estimation of task hours for projects.

\r

•             Feasibility analysis and cost benefit analysis.

\r

•             Customer requirements management

\r

•             Other responsibilities as required.

Position: Java Developer

Location: Santa Barbara, CA

Duration: 1 - 3 Month Contract

Rate: Name It!



GENERAL SUMMARY OF DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Under the general supervision of the UDEV Project lead, provide enterprise scale application development support for the UDEV Gift Processing Project. The following are requirements of the position:

Expert knowledge of J2EE architecture

Able to spend a large percentage of the day independently developing code in the Java language

Understands OO principles and design patterns

Have an in-depth understanding of the Spring Framework, Hibernate and Struts



Have in-depth understanding of the following:

Java EE 6

JAVA Servlets, JSP, Struts, Hibernate, Spring, AJAX, JOTM

XML, HTML, JSTL, JavaScript

Eclipse IDE

SVN, Ant, JUnit, Bamboo, JasperReports, iText

Tomcat, Apache

MS SQL Server



Duties done 85% of the time:

Software Implementation Support:

Independently responsible for systems analysis, design, programming, and report generation:

Utilizes Java and SQL to implement UDEV requirements

Utilizes SQL and other test tools to verify and validate that code executes as intended



Performs as part of a team on large/complex tasks.
Performs all aspects of system development lifecycle including:

Requirements definition/analysis/derivation

Impact assessment

Solution design

Code implementation

System test to ensure functionality and requirements compliance

System documentation for all phases of the lifecycle

Support the definition and implementation of standardized system development processes modeled after industry standard software engineering practices



Duties done 15% of the time:

Other duties:

Will be assigned special projects and a variety of administrative tasks. Attends staff or group meetings, and other tasks such as system documentation and baseline maintenance

Position Description

\r

Designs, develops, and implements web-based Java applications to support business requirements. Follows approved life cycle methodologies, creates design documents, and performs program coding and testing. Resolves technical issues through troubleshooting, debugging, research, and investigation.  Familiar with software development concepts, practices, and procedures (i.e. Java, EJB 3.0, JSP, JSF, HTML, SQL, Javascript). Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. 

\r

Principle Duties and Responsibilities:

\r
    \r
  • Experience in building enterprise software or large scale web application required
    • \r
  • Strong Java and J EE software development required
    • \r
  • Experience in servlets and JSP development required
    • \r
  • Hands-on experience with EJB3 or ORM software (hibernate, toplink, JDO, etc) required
    • \r
  • Ability to work across all layers of the application, from back-end databases through to the user interface
    • \r
  • In-depth knowledge with relational database, such SQL Server or Oracle, is required
    • \r
  • Agile/Iterative development methodology
    • \r
  • SQL; AJAX; JBoss; Jasper Reports
    • \r
  • Working knowledge of database relational design, data normalization and experience with JDBC drivers
    • \r
  • Experience in JavaServer Faces (JSF) is highly desirable
    • \r
  • Experience working on high scalable, distributed, high transaction applications is a plus
    • \r
  • Experience with creating web services or implementing client portion of web service is desirable
    • \r
  • Experience in Software as a Service (SaaS) is a plus
    • \r
  • Knowledge of design patterns is a plus
    • \r
  • Experience in JavaScript is a plus.
    • \r
\r

Job Specifications:

\r
    \r
  • A bachelors degree in Computer Science or Engineering and at least 6 years of Java experience working with server side applications, 7 years of experience can be substituted for a degree
    • \r
  • Candidates must be clearable US Citizens or hold at least an interim DOD security clearance
    • \r

Position Summary:

\r

Using object oriented programming languages and mobile development tools, the Programming Specialist or Analyst will work on new business initiatives in our Final Mile Services division. Project work will include the development and support of delivery management systems that ensure seamless customer service and improved administrative productivity, as well as the enhancement of our billing/invoicing and new customer integration systems.

\r \r \r \r\r

  

\r

Responsibilities:

\r

  

\r

Programming Specialist:

\r

Under general supervision, the incumbent determines technical user requirements and plays a key role in the development and installation of computer applications to fulfill these requirements.  Participates in project planning, analysis, design, coding, code review, unit/system testing, test scripting, and installation of software applications.

\r

  

\r

•             Produce effective, highly reusable and maintainable software application design by using best practices, design patterns, and OOAD methodology.

\r

•             Resolve critical problems under pressure and under significant time constraints.

\r

•             Meet with customers to analyze, gather, and document user requirements paying special attention to interfaces with other systems.

\r

•             Determine project scope and risk factors.

\r

•             Prioritize multiple projects simultaneously.

\r

•             Communicate with all project stakeholders on a regular basis.

\r

•             Participate in code reviews, shared modules, reusable components and various enterprise architectural decisions.

\r

•             Perform unit and system testing and create/maintain test scripts.

\r

•             Prepare user documents and train new users on software applications.

\r

•             Provide on call support as needed.

\r

  

\r

Programming Analyst:

\r

Under general supervision, the incumbent performs operational-level programming and systems analysis functions for technically difficult programming and application or software support; analyzes existing systems and procedures; determines the feasibility of data processing applications; designs and participates in the implementation of systems of computer programs; and may act as a lead analyst.

\r

  

\r

•             Design new systems or enhancements to existing systems.

\r

•             Determine source data (input), processing requirements (output), output formats, timing and cost estimates.

\r

•             Verify that system meets performance criteria.

\r

•             Design, implement, and document procedures.

\r

•             Design/modify, code, debug, test, and document moderately complex application systems.

\r

•             Install and test moderately complex software packages.

\r

•             Training users in new applications.

\r

•             Estimation of task hours for projects.

\r

•             Feasibility analysis and cost benefit analysis.

\r

•             Customer requirements management

\r

•             Other responsibilities as required.

\r

  

\r

\r\r \r \r \r

Are you a looking to launch your Information Technology career?  If so, then UPS is the place for you!

Once known as a trucking company, UPS is now recognized as a technology company with trucks and is poised for success.  Spending more than $1 billion a year on information technology, UPS provides its customers unparalleled capability in tracking and distribution intelligence.  This technological infrastructure also enables UPS to provide fully integrated Web-enabled, business-to-business solutions.

UPS Information Services, a leader in information technology, is currently seeking an Entry-Level Programmer to join our team.  If you are highly motivated with a degree in Computer Science, MIS, Mathematics, or Electrical Engineering, then UPS is a great place for you to start your career.

Job Description:

This Programmer will be working as a member of a development team responsible for a high performance, real-time application that is mission critical for UPS using Java and JavaScript.  The Programmer will assist in the management of translation & build tools.

The Programmer will be responsible for:

  • Writing design and technical specifications
  • Participating in reviews
  • Developing code
  • Developing and executing unit tests.

  • J2EE development – Intermediate
  • JavaScript – Intermediate
  • Java Programming – Intermediate
  • HTML – Beginner
  • Java Server Pages – Beginner
  • Java Beans – Beginner
  • Linux Application Development – Beginner
  • UNIX Shell – Beginner
  • EJB – Beginner
  • Time management skills
  • Work in a team environment
  • Work independently

Education: The desired Programmer will possess a degree in Computer Science, Information Technology related discipline or the equivalent in education and work experience.  Years of experience = 2-4+ years.

\r

Using object oriented programming languages and mobile development tools, the Programming Specialist or Analyst will work on new business initiatives in our Final Mile Services division. Project work will include the development and support of delivery management systems that ensure seamless customer service and improved administrative productivity, as well as the enhancement of our billing/invoicing and new customer integration systems.

\r \r \r \r\r

  

\r

Responsibilities:

\r

  

\r

Programming Specialist:

\r

Under general supervision, the incumbent determines technical user requirements and plays a key role in the development and installation of computer applications to fulfill these requirements.  Participates in project planning, analysis, design, coding, code review, unit/system testing, test scripting, and installation of software applications.

\r

  

\r

•             Produce effective, highly reusable and maintainable software application design by using best practices, design patterns, and OOAD methodology.

\r

•             Resolve critical problems under pressure and under significant time constraints.

\r

•             Meet with customers to analyze, gather, and document user requirements paying special attention to interfaces with other systems.

\r

•             Determine project scope and risk factors.

\r

•             Prioritize multiple projects simultaneously.

\r

•             Communicate with all project stakeholders on a regular basis.

\r

•             Participate in code reviews, shared modules, reusable components and various enterprise architectural decisions.

\r

•             Perform unit and system testing and create/maintain test scripts.

\r

•             Prepare user documents and train new users on software applications.

\r

•             Provide on call support as needed.

\r

  

\r

Programming Analyst:

\r

Under general supervision, the incumbent performs operational-level programming and systems analysis functions for technically difficult programming and application or software support; analyzes existing systems and procedures; determines the feasibility of data processing applications; designs and participates in the implementation of systems of computer programs; and may act as a lead analyst.

\r

  

\r

•             Design new systems or enhancements to existing systems.

\r

•             Determine source data (input), processing requirements (output), output formats, timing and cost estimates.

\r

•             Verify that system meets performance criteria.

\r

•             Design, implement, and document procedures.

\r

•             Design/modify, code, debug, test, and document moderately complex application systems.

\r

•             Install and test moderately complex software packages.

\r

•             Training users in new applications.

\r

•             Estimation of task hours for projects.

\r

•             Feasibility analysis and cost benefit analysis.

\r

•             Customer requirements management

\r

•             Other responsibilities as required.

\r

The Intermediate Java Developer is responsible for performing analysis, modification, documentation and support of daily operations for the ERP system and other applications. They will work closely with business unit members to understand business requirements and ensure that application systems properly function to meet business needs, delivering value across the organization. The position will consult with end users to identify current operation procedures, clarify program objectives, evaluate business requirements and implement innovative solutions in a fast paced team-oriented environment. This position includes designing, coding, modifying, testing, debugging, documenting, installing, and deploying application systems. Ability to work independently or in conjunction with other programmers. 

Responsibilities Include: 

• Develop, test, document, implement, and maintain Enterprise and Customized applications for departmental initiatives 

• Troubleshoot, support and maintain critical information systems. Analyze and identify time-sensitive system problems that could have an impact on business operations 

• Analyze existing processes and identify dependencies and potential break points, and recommend and implement improved technical solutions 

• Partner with internal customers to understand requirements in business terms and translate those requirements into technical solutions. This includes developing new capabilities as well as break fix 

• Convert project specs into sequence of detailed instructions & logical steps for coding in a computer processing language; applying knowledge of computer programming techniques / computer languages 

• Analyze, review, and alter program to increase operating efficiency or adapt to new requirements 

• Document program development, logic, coding, and corrections 

• Write functional specifications 

• Develop installation and operating procedures manual 

• May use computer-aided software tools in each stage of system development 

• Oversee hardware / software installation; provide technical assistance to program users 

• Plan, develop, and test document programs applying knowledge of programming techniques / computer systems 

• Evaluate user requests for new / modified programs 

• Outline steps required to develop programs using standard development methodologies 

• Capture requirements using development frameworks / tools 

• Assist in solving operating problems 

• Install and test program; monitor program performance after implementation 

Essential Skills: 

• Bachelor's Degree 

• 2 to 5 Years of Full SDLC Business Analysis Experience 

• Proficient in JAVA, JSP, Javascript, Weblogic and XML 

• Experience with Oracle or MS SQL Server 

Desired Skills: 

• Knowledge of system life cycle / application development alternatives 

• High aptitude for complex problem analysis / resolution 

• Excellent communication skills; ability to effectively present to target audience 

• Ability to effectively work with all levels of personnel within the organization 

• Detail-orientated; uses sound judgment; and is self-motivated with the ability to handle multiple tasks 

• Very good organization and time management skills </JobDescriptionText>

The FAST program, part of a firm-wide program directly sponsored by the CIO of JPMorgan Chase, was established to create an elegant, highly streamlined IT development and delivery environment. The program is segmented into 4 projects that cover everything from the automated delivery of pre-configured virtual machines to just-in-time deployment of tools to a developer desktop. The group is self-funding through a sustainable model of cost and efficiency saves which total tens of millions of Dollars each year.
 
FAST's role is to continuously accelerate the speed at which the Firm's technology teams deliver best in class, high quality business solutions, via strong technology leadership, delivery of shared services and the leverage of technology partnerships. It does this by changing the way the organization does work on a variety of fronts. One of those dimensions is the delivery of information services to development and technology users to accelerate their delivery to the business.

 
FAST Liquid Infrastructure encompasses the provisioning and management of virtualized environments, including virtual servers, desktops and databases.  To accomplish this, FAST LI integrates with a wide variety of enterprise systems to automate and orchestrate the provisioning processes. An application developer within the FAST group will be responsible for all areas of Software Delivery.  They will primarily be working towards the delivery of web based applications but will need to integrate with a host of backend services. The candidate must be able to work in an agile environment and demonstrate the desire to push the development and tooling in a positive direction. They must also be constantly looking for opportunities to improve the environment around them as well as their own personal skillset.
Candidate must not only be able to work on a team but actively look to engage in the team process and subsequent success.

Classification:  Programmer/Analyst Compensation:  $80,000.00 to $90,000.00 per year DESCRIPTION OF THE ROLE This position is for the Rapid Response Team in the Product Technologies department and reports to the Manager of RRT team. The Rapid Response Team (RRT) delivers quick, innovative and efficient solutions against high level requirements within a limited scope, leveraging superior technical and business skills, aggressive work ethic and common sense within the framework of a streamlined process. Project profiles include custom web properties/capability, proof-of-concept and throwaway test solutions, mobile application delivery, bolt-on solutions to core services and other similar projects. The Rapid Response Team (RRT) delivers quick, innovative and efficient solutions against high level requirements within a limited scope, leveraging superior technical and business skills, aggressive work ethic and common sense within the framework of a streamlined process. RRT developers often handle the entire project themselves, in collaboration with our business leads (Product Marketing, Sales, and Account Management etc.) all the way through delivering a build for production deploy. This position involves working with the development team and other technical teams to develop, test and deploy high availability and redundant web-based and desktop applications deployed in a multi-tier clustered environment.

  • Identify software requirements and estimate timelines.
  • Ensure a smooth and reliable integration of system components
  • Perform Unit Testing on code and work with SQA personnel to ensure software quality.
  • Support production applications and troubleshoot bugs.

Java Developer Qualifications:

Candidates need to bring at least 2-3 years of experience participating in the complete software development process from requirements gathering through deployment and maintenance.  Other expectations include at least a year or two of expertise with the following:

  • Object-oriented analysis and design concepts and techniques.
  • Java technologies such as J2SE, Swing, JDBC, Java Servlets, JSP
  • Application servers such as Tomcat, Jboss, or other
  • Web Services (SOAP, RESTful)
  • Relational databases such as PostgreSQL, MySQL, or Oracle
  • HTML, CSS, JavaScript, XML and other related technologies
  • JUnit or other related testing frameworks
  • Version control experience (i.e. SVN) and build tools (i.e. ANT).
  • Knowledge of Data Structures, Design Patterns, Coding Practices, and emerging technologies.
  • Education: Bachelor’s in Computer Science or related field.

As an Application Developer, you will provide high quality technology solutions that address business needs by developing applications within mature technology environments. You will utilize mature (3rd or 4th Generation) programming methodologies and languages and adhere to coding standards, procedures and techniques while contributing to the technical code documentation. You will participate in project planning sessions with project managers, business analysts and team members to analyze business requirements and outline the proposed IT solution. You will participate in design reviews and provide input to the design recommendations; incorporate security requirements into design; and provide input to information/data flow, and understand and comply to Project Life Cycle Methodology in all planning steps. You will also adhere to IT Control Policies throughout design, development and testing and incorporate Corporate Architectural Standards into application design specifications. Additionally, you will document the detailed application specifications, translate technical requirements into programmed application modules and develop/Enhance software application modules. You will participate in code reviews and ensure that all solutions are aligned to pre-defined architectural specifications; identify/troubleshoot application code-related issues; and review and provide feedback to the final user documentation.

\rL-3 C2S2 is looking for a software engineer to join our team in either Arlington, VA or Charleston, SC. The project will include Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), user interface, communications, database and security software development. This development program follows an agile development life cycle to rapidly deliver solutions and employs scrum teams equipped with current state of the art technologies, processes and development environments.
\r
\rDescription
\r
\rCome join our exciting and rapidly growing L-3 Command and Control Systems and Software (C2S2) family in beautiful historical Charleston SC. L-3 C2S2 Division is a leading provider of C4ISR enterprise architectures and software, applications and portal development. We have recently won a number of new and long-term contracts making long-term growth opportunities at L-3 C2S2 Charleston plentiful. Over the past year, we have more than doubled our technical staff and we are still growing!
\r
\rL-3 C2S2 has immediate openings for Java Software Developers on the Veterans Benefits Management System (VBMS) program. Potential for Relocation Assistance and Sign On Bonus! The VBMS program is a multi-year effort to transition the current paper-based Veterans claims process to a paperless solution which will reduce the average time for veteran benefits claim processing, reduce the number of claims in the VBA backlog, and automate claims tracking. The program will include Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), user interface, communications, database and security software development. This development program follows an agile development life cycle to rapidly deliver solutions and employs scrum teams equipped with current state of the art technologies, processes and development environments.
\r
\rDESIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS:
\r
\r
    \r
  • Knowledge of Java Server Frameworks (Spring) and Java Persistence Frameworks (Hibernate)\r
  • Development with Databases, particularly Oracle 11g,\r
  • J2EE - EJB, JMS, JCA, JTA, JDBC, Persistence/Hibernate, HTTP/SOAP, XSD, JAXB, and XSLT\r
  • Understanding of web optimization techniques (server/client side caching, compression, etc)\r
  • Web service design, testing and implementation\r
  • Solid understanding of web data formats (xml, json)\r
  • Coding skills in Javascript, SQL, and knowledge of HTTP. TCP/IP and network programming a plus\r
  • Knowledge of Web Services Interoperability, WS-* standards and ability to suggest, criticize and formulate solutions during architectural meetings a plus.

Advance America Cash Advance centers has an exciting opportunity for a Java Developer who will be responsible for the design and development of software enhancements, extensions and defect corrections as well as the integration of new features and products into our corporate web applications. Individual will work in an Agile development environment where core applications were recently ported from WebLogic/Java 1.4 to JBoss/Java 1.6. Applicant must have the ability to rapidly assimilate new technologies and be able to communicate effectively with various teams.  This is a full time and direct hire role in Spartanburg, SC  
\r
\rJOB RESPONSIBILITIES – 

\r
    \r
  • Write software that provides new or modifies existing business functionality by incorporating all aspects of the J2EE architecture. \r
  • Write PL/SQL procedures and functions against Oracle database for data support and security to web applications.\r
  • Working with Service Oriented Architecture (SOA) systems and concepts, and enabling technologies.\r
  • Refractor web pages to comply with defined conventions to improve usability and overall presentation efficiency. \r
  • Develop test procedures at a unit and integration level to ensure compliance with Advance America standards and development practices. \r
